%p.project__para-1 3DSANDBOX is an interactive, realtime 3D art experience. It requires one group of users to interact with a miniature set, which is being filmed and displayed to a second group of users using an experimental single camera 3D capture system, that relies on temporal manipulation to extract 3D from a single constantly moving camera.

%div.project__image-container
	- 4.upto(6) do |index|
		= tag :img, src: "/assets/images/projects/sandbox/sandbox#{index}.jpg",class:'project__image'

%p.project__para-2 3DSANDBOX aims to capture an uninhibited, playful and childlike interactivity, whilst creating a space for audience performance and participation. It is also an inquiry into the nature of vision and sight, and the human sensory experience.

%div.project__image-container
	- 7.upto(9) do |index|
		= tag :img, src: "/assets/images/projects/sandbox/sandbox#{index}.jpg",class:'project__image'

%p.project__para-3 3DSANDBOX was on display at the Black and White Gallery at CalArts as a part of the Varia Stereoscopic Group Show on December 7th, 2017. It was created by James Anderson, Clay Burton and Shaurjya Banerjee.

