%h1.project__heading 3DSANDBOX 2

%div.project__single__image
	= tag :img, :src => "/assets/images/projects/sandbox2/sandbox2-1.jpg", class:'single__image'

%p.project__para 3DSANDBOX 2 was on display at the CalArts Digital Arts Expo on May 3rd, 2018. It was an iteration on the original 3DSANDBOX concept and was made to use 360 camera travel. 

%div.project__image-container
	- 4.upto(6) do |index|
		= tag :img, src: "/assets/images/projects/sandbox2/sandbox2-#{index}.jpg",class:'project__image'

%p.project__para The set for 3DSANDBOX 2 was circular and its walls were covered with animation cells and backgrounds, that created three distinct scenes, with a small gap in the walls for the audience themselves to be picked up by the camera feed as the fourth scene. 

%div.project__image-container
	- 1.upto(3) do |index|
		= tag :img, src: "/assets/images/projects/sandbox2/sandbox2-#{index}.jpg",class:'project__image'

%p.project__para The set was populated with a number of puppets and toys as well as scenic elements like trees at a variety of different scales, and the camera was located at the very center of the set, located very close to the surface of the table.

%p.project__para 3DSANDBOX 2 was created by James Anderson, Clay Burton and Shaurjya Banerjee.